BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:konior-research-assistant-ai-ukraine-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260723
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260724
SUMMARY:Deadline: Paid Research Assistant: AI and the War in Ukraine
DESCRIPTION:Bogna Konior\, Assistant Professor of Media Theory at NYU Shang
 hai\, is hiring a paid research assistant for a project on Ukraine and art
 ificial intelligence. The work supports a forthcoming book with MIT Press\
 , plus an independent scenario she is writing on the future of AI with the
  war as a lens. WHAT THE WORK LOOKS LIKE: going month-by-month through new
 s archives (New York Times\, Reuters\, Financial Times\, and specialist ou
 tlets)\, annotating and cataloguing coverage of AI\, drones\, and autonomo
 us systems in the war\, plus other developments she will direct you to\; b
 uilding and maintaining a structured Notion database covering chronology\,
  companies\, industries\, and key actors\; and organizing and editing her 
 existing notes. WHO SHE IS LOOKING FOR: interest in and general knowledge 
 of AI\; prior research and annotation experience\, careful and detail-orie
 nted\, no sloppy citations\; comfortable with Notion and with AI tools\; U
 krainian language skill a strong plus (not required)\; familiarity with AI
 \, war\, tech\, and geopolitics news sources is great. Remote-friendly\, s
 tart ASAP. She will also consider people with no prior experience\, as wel
 l as current and previous students. TERMS: USD 18 per hour\, 10-15 hours p
 er week\, flexible schedule. TO APPLY: email bogna@nyu.edu with a short in
 troduction and background (link to website\, socials\, CV\, LinkedIn\, or 
 portfolio if you have one)\; where you are based and your weekly availabil
 ity\; and one recent AI-related story\, company\, or development you find 
 interesting and why (a vibe check). Bonus: a sample of past research or wr
 iting if you have it.\n\nOrganisation: Bogna Konior (NYU Shanghai)\nLocati
 on: Remote-friendly.\nAward: USD 18 per hour\; 10-15 hours per week\, flex
 ible schedule.\nDuration: Ongoing part-time research assistantship\; start
  as soon as possible.\n\nMore: https://www.instagram.com/p/Dak-bwACIMt/?ut
 m_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.instagram.com/p/Dak-bwACIMt/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugr
 antdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote-friendly.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:serpentine-live-programmes-curator-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260710
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260711
SUMMARY:Deadline: Serpentine Galleries: Live Programmes Curator
DESCRIPTION:Serpentine Galleries seeks an experienced interdisciplinary Liv
 e Programmes Curator to initiate\, develop\, and produce a year-round live
  programme that extends and activates the gallery's exhibitions and curato
 rial vision through talks\, performances\, participatory experiences\, and
  cross-disciplinary live formats. Building on Serpentine's flagship strand
 s (the annual Marathons\, Park Nights\, Serpentine Cinema\, and Study Days
 )\, the curator will run a live programme alongside and through onsite exh
 ibitions\, working closely with the Programmes\, Production\, and Audience
  teams. RESPONSIBILITIES: conceive\, curate\, and deliver live events (tal
 ks\, performances\, workshops\, screenings\, new formats)\; develop format
 s that bring visual artists into dialogue with dance\, music\, film\, lite
 rature\, technology\, design\, and social practice\; lead planning and del
 ivery on time and on budget\; and develop programming that attracts new\, 
 diverse\, and multi-generational audiences onsite and online. REQUIREMENTS
 : significant experience curating and/or producing live programmes in a ga
 llery\, museum\, festival\, performance\, or cultural context\; a strong i
 nterdisciplinary curatorial approach across multiple artistic forms\; exce
 llent project management\, budgeting\, and scheduling\; strong communicati
 on and collaboration\; and deep knowledge of contemporary art and current 
 cultural discourse. TERMS: permanent role (3-month probationary period)\; 
 hybrid working (3 days office\, 2 remote)\; 25 days annual leave rising to
  30 after 5 years plus 8 bank holidays\; auto-enrolment pension\, season-t
 icket loan\, and Cycle2Work scheme. SALARY: GBP 45\,000 per annum. TO APPL
 Y: submit a CV and cover letter addressing how your skills fit the role\, 
 examples of relevant experience\, and what attracts you to Serpentine. DEA
 DLINE: midnight\, 10 July 2026\; first-stage interviews w/c 20 July 2026\,
  second-stage w/c 27 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Serpentine Galleries\nLoc
 ation: London\, United Kingdom\; hybrid working (3 days in office\, 2 remo
 te).\nAward: GBP 45\,000 per year. Permanent role (3-month probation). No 
 application fee.\nDuration: Permanent appointment\; hybrid\, 3 days office
  / 2 remote. 25 days annual leave rising to 30 after 5 years\, plus 8 bank
  holidays.\n\nMore: https://serpentinegallery.careers.hibob.com/jobs/89899
 306-2f4d-41b1-b6c9-af85294de402?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
URL:https://serpentinegallery.careers.hibob.com/jobs/89899306-2f4d-41b1-b6c
 9-af85294de402?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:London\, United Kingdom\; hybrid working (3 days in office\, 2 rem
 ote).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:queer-art-design-grant-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260814
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260815
SUMMARY:Deadline: Queer|Art Design Grant 2026 (Inaugural)
DESCRIPTION:The Queer|Art Design Grant is a new initiative from Queer|Art s
 upporting projects that explore queer histories\, legacies\, and futures w
 hile providing visibility and opportunity for emerging LGBTQ+ design talen
 t. AWARDS: two USD 10\,000 grants to emerging queer creatives across the d
 esign industry\, described as the largest cash grant for LGBTQ+ designers 
 in the country. ELIGIBILITY: US-based designers working across a variety o
 f disciplines\, including graphic design\, architecture and landscape arch
 itecture\, industrial and product design\, fashion\, textile and wearables
 \, digital design\, service design\, furniture and home decor\, materials 
 research\, interior design\, and more. In its inaugural year the grant is 
 judged by a panel of designers\, curators\, architects\, and cultural lead
 ers\, including Bex McCharen\, Salome Asega\, Cristina Grajales\, Jaffer K
 olb\, and Paul Soulellis. The program is the first major initiative under 
 a new partnership between UGG and Queer|Art\; Queer|Art board member and c
 reative strategist Fran Tirado serves as Community Curator. Winners will b
 e announced at Queer|Art's Annual Party in Fall 2026. DEADLINE: 14 August 
 2026. Apply via https://www.queer-art.org/design-grant.\n\nOrganisation: Q
 ueer|Art (in partnership with UGG)\nLocation: United States\; open to US-b
 ased emerging queer/LGBTQ+ designers.\nAward: Two USD 10\,000 grants (desc
 ribed as the largest cash grant for LGBTQ+ designers in the US). No applic
 ation fee.\nDuration: One-off grant\; winners announced at Queer|Art's Ann
 ual Party\, Fall 2026\n\nMore: https://www.queer-art.org/design-grant?utm_
 source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.queer-art.org/design-grant?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:United States\; open to US-based emerging queer/LGBTQ+ designers.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:new-emergence-art-prize-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260803
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260804
SUMMARY:Deadline: New Emergence Art Prize 2026
DESCRIPTION:The New Emergence Art Prize 2026 is an international open call 
 for emerging artists\, presented by New Emergence Art. There is no set the
 me and work may be submitted in any medium. AWARDS: a prize fund worth ove
 r GBP 5\,000 across nine awards supporting artists through cash prizes\, a
 rtist materials\, mentoring\, and a residency\, including a GBP 1\,000 Gra
 nd Prize\, a two-week NG Art Creative Residency in Provence\, France (wort
 h EUR 2\,000)\, a GBP 300 Founder's Prize cash award\, and materials or su
 bscription awards from Staedtler UK\, Rosemary & Co\, GreatArt\, Michael H
 arding\, and The Art Ladder. ELIGIBILITY: open internationally to emerging
  artists\; entrants may submit up to three original artworks that represen
 t the quality\, originality and direction of their practice. Final selecti
 ons are made by an independent judging panel considering concept\, executi
 on\, originality and impact. Shortlisted artists are featured in an online
  exhibition running 11 August to 7 September 2026. NOTE: there is a paid e
 ntry fee (amount set at the entry step). DEADLINE: 3 August 2026\, 23:59 B
 ST. Apply via https://www.newemergenceart.com/apply.\n\nOrganisation: New 
 Emergence Art\nLocation: International\; open worldwide. Shortlist shown i
 n an online exhibition.\nAward: Prize fund worth over GBP 5\,000 across ni
 ne awards\, including a GBP 1\,000 Grand Prize cash award\, a two-week NG 
 Art Creative Residency in Provence\, France (worth EUR 2\,000)\, a GBP 300
  Founder's Prize cash award\, and materials or subscription awards from St
 aedtler UK\, Rosemary & Co\, GreatArt\, Michael Harding\, and The Art Ladd
 er. NOTE: there is a paid entry fee.\nDuration: One-off prize\; shortliste
 d artists shown in an online exhibition 11 August to 7 September 2026\n\nM
 ore: https://www.newemergenceart.com/apply?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.newemergenceart.com/apply?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrant
 desk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:International\; open worldwide. Shortlist shown in an online exhib
 ition.
END:VEVENT
