UID:create-nsw-stories-matter-literary-fellowships-2026@artificialnouveau.g
 ithub.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260727
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260728
SUMMARY:Deadline: Create NSW: Stories Matter NSW Literary Fellowships 2026
DESCRIPTION:Stories Matter is a new NSW literary fellowship program from Cr
 eate NSW\, administered by Writing NSW\, awarding ten fellowships of AUD 5
 0\,000 each to support NSW-based writers to focus on a major new work over
  a 12-month period. The 2026 round funds four emerging\, three mid-career\
 , and three established writers working across prose fiction\, poetry\, il
 lustration\, graphic novels\, and playwriting. ELIGIBILITY: writers must b
 e based in New South Wales\; open to writers at any career stage within th
 e three tiers (not open to applicants outside NSW). No application fee. DE
 ADLINE: 27 July 2026\, 2:00pm AEST. Apply via the Create NSW grants portal
 .\n\nOrganisation: Create NSW (administered by Writing NSW)\nLocation: New
  South Wales\, Australia\; applicants must be NSW-based.\nAward: AUD 50\,0
 00 per fellowship\, 10 fellowships awarded (4 emerging\, 3 mid-career\, 3 
 established). No application fee.\nDuration: 12-month fellowship\n\nMore: 
 https://www.nsw.gov.au/grants-and-funding/stories-matter-nsw-literary-fell
 owships?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.nsw.gov.au/grants-and-funding/stories-matter-nsw-literary-f
 ellowships?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:New South Wales\, Australia\; applicants must be NSW-based.
END:VEVENT
