DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260806
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260807
SUMMARY:Deadline: Fondazione Prada Film Fund 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Fondazione Prada Film Fund is an annual EUR 1.5 million fun
 d backing 10 to 12 feature-length films (fiction\, documentary\, and anima
 tion\, 65 minutes or longer) across development\, production\, and post-pr
 oduction. ELIGIBILITY: independent producers and production companies with
  a track record (approximately two or more feature films premiered at majo
 r international festivals) and partial financing already secured\; this is
  aimed at established independent producers\, NOT individual emerging arti
 sts. DEADLINES: 6 August 2026 for projects in production\; 10 September 20
 26 for development and post-production projects (this card uses the earlie
 st deadline). Apply via the Fondazione Prada Film Fund page. NOTE: the fun
 der's primary page was not directly reachable at time of entry\; dates cor
 roborated via industry trade press (Screen\, Cineuropa). Verify the exact 
 track deadline before applying.\n\nOrganisation: Fondazione Prada\nLocatio
 n: Milan\, Italy-based fund\; open worldwide to independent producers and 
 production companies.\nAward: EUR 1.5 million total pool supporting 10 to 
 12 feature films. Development grants EUR 15\,000 to 80\,000\; production g
 rants EUR 30\,000 to 250\,000\; post-production grants EUR 40\,000 to 100\
 ,000. No application fee.\nDuration: Feature film funding (development\, p
 roduction\, or post-production)\n\nMore: https://www.fondazioneprada.org/f
 ilm-fund/?lang=en&utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referra
 l
URL:https://www.fondazioneprada.org/film-fund/?lang=en&utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Milan\, Italy-based fund\; open worldwide to independent producers
  and production companies.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:alabama-clotilda-memorial-public-art-commission-2026@artificialnouveau.
 github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260809
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260810
SUMMARY:Deadline: Alabama Historical Commission: Clotilda Memorial Public A
 rt Commission
DESCRIPTION:The Alabama Historical Commission\, working with public-art con
 sultancy Forecast Public Art\, seeks proposals for a major memorial artwor
 k honoring the survivors of the Clotilda\, the last known ship to illegall
 y traffic enslaved Africans to the United States (1860). The memorial will
  convey the survivors' lives and legacies and be developed through collabo
 rative community engagement with historic Africatown\, the community found
 ed by Clotilda survivors\, and the broader diaspora. ELIGIBILITY: open to 
 artists of all disciplines\, including time-based and media artists\; indi
 viduals and teams\; open internationally. BUDGET: USD 2\,000\,000 total pr
 oject budget. DEADLINE: 9 August 2026\, 11:59pm CST. Applications are hand
 led through the CODAworx RFQ platform\; find the Clotilda Memorial listing
  in the CODAworx opportunities index. Verify the listing details on CODAwo
 rx before applying.\n\nOrganisation: Alabama Historical Commission (with F
 orecast Public Art)\nLocation: Africatown\, Mobile\, Alabama\, USA\; open 
 to artists internationally.\nAward: USD 2\,000\,000 total project budget f
 or a paid public art commission. No application fee.\nDuration: Permanent 
 public art commission\n\nMore: https://www.codaworx.com/rfp/?utm_source=ar
 tificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.codaworx.com/rfp/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm
 _medium=referral
LOCATION:Africatown\, Mobile\, Alabama\, USA\; open to artists internationa
 lly.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:padimai-onchain-artist-residency-oops-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260815
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260816
SUMMARY:Deadline: Padimai: OOPS Onchain Artist Residency 2026
DESCRIPTION:OOPS (Origin Of Primary Source) is the first edition of Padimai
  Art and Tech Studio's Onchain Artist Residency\, a three-month remote res
 idency inviting art practitioners to critically and creatively engage with
  NFTs as artistic registers and as systems of knowledge\, documentation\, 
 and access. Five practitioners are selected. SUPPORT: SGD 15\,000 honorari
 um per artist\, plus SGD 5\,000 per artist for documentation. The residenc
 y is remote\, with community engagement designed through online meetings\;
  at the end\, participants deliver three NFTs developed during the residen
 cy to Padimai. ELIGIBILITY: individual creative practitioners working at t
 he intersection of art\, technology\, and blockchain\; open internationall
 y. RESIDENCY: 20 September to 20 December 2026. DEADLINE: 15 August 2026. 
 Apply via the residency page.\n\nOrganisation: Padimai Art and Tech Studio
 \nLocation: Remote residency (Padimai is based in Singapore)\; open intern
 ationally.\nAward: SGD 15\,000 honorarium per artist plus an additional SG
 D 5\,000 per artist for documentation (audio\, video\, photography). Five 
 practitioners selected. No application fee.\nDuration: 3 months (20 Septem
 ber to 20 December 2026)\n\nMore: https://padimai.net/onchain-artist-resid
 ency/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://padimai.net/onchain-artist-residency/?utm_source=artificialnouv
 eaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote residency (Padimai is based in Singapore)\; open internatio
 nally.
END:VEVENT
