DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260831
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
SUMMARY:Deadline: Liu Shiming Art Foundation: Artist Grants 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Liu Shiming Art Foundation's annual Artist Grants (fourth e
 dition) award up to five grants of USD 5\,000 each to early-career visual 
 artists to create new work exploring connections between traditional\, cul
 tural\, or historical influences and contemporary artistic practice. ELIGI
 BILITY: visual artists in the first decade of their career (two to ten yea
 rs practicing professionally)\; applicants must have received a studio-art
 s degree between 2016 and 2024\, or had their debut gallery or juried-exhi
 bition show between 2016 and 2026. Open to artists of any country\; the ap
 plication and all supporting materials must be in English. TIMELINE: appli
 cations open 1 June 2026\; close 31 August 2026\; recipients notified by 2
  December 2026. Apply via the Foundation's grants page.\n\nOrganisation: L
 iu Shiming Art Foundation\nLocation: Open to artists of any country\; appl
 ication must be in English.\nAward: Up to five grants of USD 5\,000 each. 
 Disbursed in two payments (USD 3\,000 by 15 January 2027 and USD 2\,000 on
  project completion). No application fee.\nDuration: Project grant for new
  work\n\nMore: https://www.lsmartfund.org/grants?utm_source=artificialnouv
 eaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.lsmartfund.org/grants?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk
 &utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Open to artists of any country\; application must be in English.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:iias-asia-in-the-world-fellowship-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260910
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260911
SUMMARY:Deadline: IIAS: Asia in the World Fellowship Programme 2027-2028
DESCRIPTION:The Asia in the World Fellowship Programme\, run by the Interna
 tional Institute for Asian Studies (IIAS) at Leiden University\, is a nine
 -month\, two-phase fellowship pairing a residency at a partner institution
  in Asia\, Africa\, Latin America\, or Europe (Phase 1) with six months in
  residence at IIAS in Leiden\, the Netherlands (Phase 2). The programme su
 pports interdisciplinary\, humanities- and social-science-based research e
 ngaging Asia and its connections with the wider world. SUPPORT during the 
 Leiden phase: EUR 1\,250 per month stipend\, EUR 1\,200 per month housing 
 allowance\, and a travel grant\; the Phase 1 stipend is provided by the co
 -host institution. ELIGIBILITY: scholars and researchers worldwide\; open 
 internationally. APPLICATIONS open 1 July 2026\; deadline 10 September 202
 6. Apply via the IIAS fellowships page. NOTE: dates confirmed via secondar
 y sources at time of entry (the funder page was not directly reachable)\; 
 verify before applying.\n\nOrganisation: International Institute for Asian
  Studies (IIAS)\, Leiden University\nLocation: Two phases: a partner insti
 tution in Asia\, Africa\, Latin America\, or Europe (Phase 1)\, then Leide
 n\, Netherlands (Phase 2). Open internationally.\nAward: Leiden phase: EUR
  1\,250 per month stipend plus EUR 1\,200 per month housing allowance\, pl
 us a travel grant\; the Phase 1 stipend at the co-host institution is set 
 by that institution. No application fee.\nDuration: 9 months (two phases)\
 n\nMore: https://www.iias.asia/fellowships/asia-in-the-world?utm_source=ar
 tificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.iias.asia/fellowships/asia-in-the-world?utm_source=artifici
 alnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Two phases: a partner institution in Asia\, Africa\, Latin America
 \, or Europe (Phase 1)\, then Leiden\, Netherlands (Phase 2). Open interna
 tionally.
END:VEVENT
