 thub.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260831
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
SUMMARY:Deadline: AIxDESIGN: Grain\, Open Call for Critical AI Literacy Rec
 ipes
DESCRIPTION:Grain is a cookbook of critical and creative AI literacy exerci
 ses for educators across audiovisual and creative practice\, co-produced b
 y AIxDESIGN and the Netherlands Film Academy and led by Nadia Piet. The op
 en call collects 'recipes': tried-and-tested group exercises for the class
 room or workshop that get people thinking critically and making creatively
  with AI. Exercises can be hands-on or analog\, 15 minutes or a full day\,
  beginner or advanced\; the one hard requirement is that someone else can 
 read your recipe and run it themselves. Examples of what might fit: hands-
 on experiments with specific AI tools (image generators\, chatbots\, code 
 assistants\, video models)\; analog activities that reveal computational l
 ogic through embodied practice\; critical readings\, watchings\, or listen
 ings with structured discussion\; provocations\, games\, or role-plays tha
 t get at how AI sees\, thinks\, or makes\; and exercises that help people 
 figure out how they want to relate to AI in their own practice. WHAT YOU G
 ET: your recipe formatted and credited to you in the first edition of Grai
 n\, a print copy when it lands\, and an invite to the launch. Everything i
 s published under CC BY-SA 4.0 so the work can travel and you keep authors
 hip. FEE: this round offers a need-based fee for freelance and independent
  practitioners of EUR 150 per recipe\; if making the time would be hard wi
 thout it\, email hello@aixdesign.co with your proposal. After this round t
 he call stays open but the fee will not. LIVE SESSION: an optional 30-minu
 te live session on Wednesday 12 August 2026 at 16:00 CEST lets you bring a
  rough exercise and turn it into a recipe on the spot with the Grain Recip
 e Converter (online\, sign up at luma.com/84w148in). Submissions are open 
 until the end of August 2026\; Grain publishes March 2027. Submit via the 
 form\; questions to hello@aixdesign.co.\n\nOrganisation: AIxDESIGN\, co-pr
 oduced with the Netherlands Film Academy\nLocation: Remote/online\; open t
 o educators and practitioners based anywhere\nAward: Need-based fee of EUR
  150 per recipe for freelance and independent practitioners (email hello@a
 ixdesign.co if the time would be hard to make without it). Your recipe is 
 formatted and credited to you in the first edition of Grain\, plus a print
  copy and an invite to the launch. Published under CC BY-SA 4.0\; you keep
  authorship.\nDuration: One-off contribution\; Grain publishes March 2027\
 n\nMore: https://nadiapiet.notion.site/Open-Call-Grain-Cookbook-for-Critic
 al-AI-Literacy-38e37d003833804380acd027b6041d5a?utm_source=artificialnouve
 augrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://nadiapiet.notion.site/Open-Call-Grain-Cookbook-for-Critical-AI-
 Literacy-38e37d003833804380acd027b6041d5a?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote/online\; open to educators and practitioners based anywhere
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:aixdesign-kb-national-library-ai-exhibition-2026@artificialnouveau.gith
 ub.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260831
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
SUMMARY:Deadline: AIxDESIGN x KB: Open Call for Sessions\, (Art)works and P
 erformances
DESCRIPTION:AIxDESIGN and the KB (Koninklijke Bibliotheek\, the National Li
 brary of the Netherlands) are building an exhibition and public programme 
 about AI\, made from the national collection\, at the KB in The Hague. Nad
 ia Piet is Creative Lead with the AIxDESIGN community\, co-presented with 
 the KB. The premise: long before neural nets\, libraries were the machines
  we built to organise human knowledge\, and the show uses the KB's collect
 ion to look at what AI is\, where it comes from\, and how it connects to t
 he older story of how we store\, sort\, and search what we know. Part of t
 he show lives in the KB Atelier\, with talks\, workshops\, and screenings 
 alongside\, intended as AI literacy you can wander into. WHAT THEY WANT: w
 ork that engages AI in some way (critical\, creative\, hands-on\, or playf
 ul)\; bonus if it also speaks to archives\, libraries\, or how we store an
 d sort knowledge\, though you do not need to touch the KB's collection to 
 take part. You may pitch to more than one track: (A) SOMETHING FOR THE OPE
 NING NIGHT\, a performance\, talk\, screening\, tour\, ritual\, booth\, ga
 me\, or other experience for the November 2026 opening\, fee EUR 1\,500 to
  2\,000\; (B) A SESSION IN THE EVENTS PROGRAMME\, a workshop or other sess
 ion once during the three-month run\, around 2.5 to 4 hours\, fee EUR 2\,0
 00 to 2\,500\; (C) AN (ART)WORK FOR THE EXHIBITION\, existing work in any 
 format (installation\, sculpture\, zine stand\, a corner of your own) stur
 dy enough for a public area with daily traffic\, honorarium EUR 200 to 400
  including licensing and production\; (D) SOMETHING ELSE ENTIRELY\, pitch 
 it anyway. WHO: artists\, designers\, researchers\, technologists\, perfor
 mers\, musicians\, archivists\, or educators working around AI\, data\, li
 braries\, or cultural heritage\; no finished idea or polished CV needed\, 
 just a clear\, specific pitch. You can be based anywhere and they especial
 ly welcome people outside the Netherlands\; the show is in-person in The H
 ague and the fee stays the same wherever you are coming from. HOW TO APPLY
 : send a short pitch through the form (which track\, your idea in a paragr
 aph or two\, roughly what it would need\, and a link to your work)\; takes
  about five minutes\, no full application required. Deadline: end of Augus
 t 2026. Questions to hello@aixdesign.co.\n\nOrganisation: AIxDESIGN\, co-p
 resented with the Koninklijke Bibliotheek (KB)\, National Library of the N
 etherlands\nLocation: KB\, The Hague\, Netherlands (in-person exhibition a
 nd programme)\; pitches welcome from people based anywhere\nAward: Fees by
  track: opening-night experience EUR 1\,500 to 2\,000\; a session in the e
 vents programme EUR 2\,000 to 2\,500\; an existing (art)work for the exhib
 ition EUR 200 to 400 honorarium (including licensing and production). The 
 fee stays the same wherever you are based.\nDuration: Exhibition runs Nove
 mber 2026 to February 2027\; opening event November 2026\n\nMore: https://
 nadiapiet.notion.site/Open-Call-AIxDESIGN-x-KB-Sessions-Art-works-More-38f
 37d0038338102b128c57cbeb16d2d?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_me
 dium=referral
URL:https://nadiapiet.notion.site/Open-Call-AIxDESIGN-x-KB-Sessions-Art-wor
 ks-More-38f37d0038338102b128c57cbeb16d2d?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrant
 desk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:KB\, The Hague\, Netherlands (in-person exhibition and programme)\
 ; pitches welcome from people based anywhere
END:VEVENT
