UID:atheras-nicosia-ludic-lab-toyful-music-festival-2026@artificialnouveau.
 github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Deadline: Atheras: Nicosia Ludic Lab for Composers\, Toyful Music F
 estival 2026
DESCRIPTION:Atheras Peoples and Cultures invites composers and performer-re
 searchers to apply for the Nicosia Ludic Lab\, a 31-day international resi
 dency dedicated to exploring 'play' as a compositional and performative me
 thodology in contemporary music. Building on the artistic vision of the To
 yful Music Festival\, the residency creates a focused environment where ex
 perimentation\, precision\, and imagination coexist\, redefining how music
  is conceived\, structured\, and performed. The residency runs in Nicosia\
 , Cyprus\, from 23 October to 22 November 2026\, and participants develop 
 new ensemble works that directly shape the artistic programme of the Toyfu
 l Music Festival 2026. ELIGIBILITY: applications are open to individual ar
 tists (proposals from duets or collectives will not be considered) based i
 n a Creative Europe country\, who must demonstrate a strong interest in ex
 perimental\, ensemble-based practices. SELECTED RESIDENTS RECEIVE: full fi
 nancial support (travel\, accommodation\, daily allowance)\; shared accomm
 odation in central Nicosia\; continuous access to a professional ensemble\
 ; mentorship sessions and individual meetings with ensemble members\; coac
 hing sessions with composer and conductor Andys Skordis\; artistic and pro
 fessional guidance from the Atheras team\; rehearsal space and full produc
 tion support for Phase 3\; and video and audio recording of the final live
  concert for documentation and international visibility. Deadline: 15 July
  2026.\n\nOrganisation: Atheras Peoples and Cultures\nLocation: Nicosia\, 
 Cyprus\; open to individual artists based in a Creative Europe country\nAw
 ard: Full financial support: travel\, shared accommodation in central Nico
 sia\, and daily allowance. Rehearsal space and full production support pro
 vided\; final live concert recorded (video and audio) for documentation an
 d international visibility.\nDuration: 31-day residency\, 23 October to 22
  November 2026\n\nMore: https://on-the-move.org/news/atheras-nicosia-ludic
 -lab-composers-new-works-toyful-music-festival-2026-cyprus?utm_source=arti
 ficialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://on-the-move.org/news/atheras-nicosia-ludic-lab-composers-new-wo
 rks-toyful-music-festival-2026-cyprus?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdes
 k&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Nicosia\, Cyprus\; open to individual artists based in a Creative 
 Europe country
END:VEVENT
