SUMMARY:Deadline: imprint: a QTBIPOC Dance Writing Fellowship
DESCRIPTION:imprint is an annual dance writing fellowship from pateldancewo
 rks for emerging QTBIPOC (queer\, trans\, Black\, Indigenous\, and people 
 of color) dance writers based in the San Francisco Bay Area. Artistic Dire
 ctor Bhumi B Patel supports three selected fellows with writing and publis
 hing mentorship and professional development over a program year. Each fel
 low receives a USD 500 stipend and commits roughly 30 hours across six coh
 ort meetings that include readings\, discussions\, writing feedback\, and 
 guest speakers. Fellows attend at least five Bay Area dance performances a
 nd have two to three completed pieces published on the pateldanceworks blo
 g. The program is not intended for full-time students given the time requi
 rements. There is no application fee.\n\nOrganisation: pateldanceworks\nLo
 cation: San Francisco Bay Area\, California\, United States\nAward: USD 50
 0 stipend per fellow\, plus writing and publishing mentorship\nDuration: O
 ne program year (approximately September to September)\n\nMore: https://ww
 w.pateldanceworks.org/imprint?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_me
 dium=referral
