SUMMARY:Deadline: Loghaven Artist Residency
DESCRIPTION:Loghaven Artist Residency offers practicing artists time\, spac
 e\, and resources on ninety wooded acres in Knoxville\, Tennessee. Fellows
  stay in five rehabilitated historic log cabins with access to purpose-bui
 lt studio space. Each Fellow receives an USD 850 weekly living stipend\, a
  travel subsidy on a sliding scale from USD 400 to 800\, up to USD 200 in 
 materials shipping reimbursement\, and covered room and board. Residencies
  run from 2 to 6 weeks across sessions scheduled throughout 2027. The prog
 ram is open to artists at any career stage working in architecture\, dance
 \, interdisciplinary art\, music composition\, theater\, visual art\, and 
 writing\, including collaborative groups of up to nine people. Applicants 
 must be at least 21\, live more than 120 miles from Knoxville\, and be eli
 gible to work legally in the US\; international artists and degree-seeking
  students are not eligible.\n\nOrganisation: Loghaven Artist Residency\nLo
 cation: Knoxville\, Tennessee\, USA\nAward: USD 850 weekly living stipend\
 , travel subsidy USD 400 to 800\, up to USD 200 materials shipping reimbur
 sement\, plus room and board\, housing in historic log cabins\, and studio
  space USD 25 non-refundable application fee (fee waiver available on requ
 est)\nDuration: 2 to 6 weeks depending on session\n\nMore: https://loghave
 n.org/residencies/apply/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=
 referral
