UID:vfa-sonic-connections-open-call-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260719
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260720
SUMMARY:Deadline: Sonic Connections Open Call 2027 (Villa Filanda Antonini)
DESCRIPTION:Villa Filanda Antonini (VFA) launches its Spring Open Call to s
 elect up to 4 artists and professionals for a one-month residency in March
  2027 on the theme 'Sonic Connections'\, focused on experimental music\, s
 ound art\, and performances. Hosted at Villa Filanda Antonini\, a former s
 ilk mill in Villorba\, Italy\, the project brings together four internatio
 nal artists and professionals to examine the relationship between architec
 ture\, landscape\, and collective sonic experience. ADDRESSED TO: artists\
 , performers\, curators\, designers\, and professionals not currently resi
 ding in Italy. GRANT & BENEFITS: a fully funded residency covering mentori
 ng\, accommodation\, travel costs\, production costs\, and a daily salary\
 , plus a EUR 1\,000 residency stipend. WHEN: 1-31 March 2027. HOW TO APPLY
 : complete the application form and attach a CV\, portfolio\, project prop
 osal\, and letter of reference. The VFA residency program has been selecte
 d under conditions by Culture Moves Europe\, a project funded by the Europ
 ean Union and implemented by the Goethe-Institut. Deadline: 19 July 2026\,
  23:59 CEST.\n\nOrganisation: Villa Filanda Antonini (VFA)\nLocation: Vill
 orba\, Italy (a former silk mill). Addressed to artists and professionals 
 NOT currently residing in Italy.\nAward: Fully funded residency covering m
 entoring\, accommodation\, travel costs\, production costs\, and a daily s
 alary\, plus a EUR 1\,000 residency stipend.\nDuration: One-month residenc
 y\, 1-31 March 2027.\n\nMore: https://www.vfa.art/events/sonic-connections
 -open-call-2027/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.vfa.art/events/sonic-connections-open-call-2027/?utm_source
 =artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Villorba\, Italy (a former silk mill). Addressed to artists and pr
 ofessionals NOT currently residing in Italy.
END:VEVENT
