SUMMARY:Deadline: Film London: The FLAMIN Fellowship 2026
DESCRIPTION:The FLAMIN Fellowship from Film London supports early-career ar
 tists working in moving image with a development bursary and a structured 
 year-long career-development programme. ELIGIBILITY: England-based moving-
 image artists with roughly 2 to 5 years of professional practice outside h
 igher education and at least two prior exhibited or screened works\; exclu
 des current students\, gallery-represented artists\, those with major solo
  institutional shows\, and film-industry professionals. Apply via the Film
  London FLAMIN Fellowship page by midnight on 1 June 2026.\n\nOrganisation
 : Film London (FLAMIN - Film London Artists' Moving Image Network)\, with 
 Arts Council England\nLocation: England\, UK (year-long programme with in-
 person workshops)\nAward: GBP 2\,500 project-development bursary per artis
 t\, plus a year-long programme of monthly in-person workshops\, 1:1 sessio
 ns with a production advisor\, screening and promotion\, and a peer commun
 ity. Stage-2 interviewees also receive a GBP 100 interview fee. No applica
 tion fee.\nDuration: One-year fellowship programme\n\nMore: https://filmlo
 ndon.org.uk/resource/apply-to-the-flamin-fellowship?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
