SUMMARY:Deadline: Prix Ibn Khaldoun – Léopold Sédar Senghor Translation
  Prize 2026 (OIF / ALECSO)
DESCRIPTION:The Ibn Khaldoun – Léopold Sédar Senghor Translation Prize 
 (19th edition\, 2026) is awarded jointly by the Organisation international
 e de la Francophonie (OIF) and ALECSO to recognise excellence in literary 
 and humanities/social sciences translation between French and Arabic in ei
 ther direction. Cash award: EUR 10\,000. ELIGIBILITY: open to individual t
 ranslators\, universities and higher education institutions\, research cen
 tres\, national associations and unions\, and publishing houses from the A
 rab world and Francophone space. Works must be literary or humanities/soci
 al sciences texts translated between French and Arabic (either direction)\
 , published within 3 years prior to the application year\, and must be a f
 irst translation of the original. Self-published or photocopied works excl
 uded. One work maximum per candidate. Applications submitted exclusively e
 lectronically\; required materials: CV\, presentation of translation work\
 , copies of both translated and original texts. Deadline: 30 June 2026. Ap
 ply at https://appelsaprojets.francophonie.org/fr/applications/soutien-a-l
 a-circulation-des-biens-et-mobilite-des-artistes.\n\nOrganisation: Organis
 ation internationale de la Francophonie (OIF) and Arab League Educational\
 , Cultural and Scientific Organization (ALECSO)\nLocation: International (
 Francophone zone and Arab world)\nAward: EUR 10\,000 (funded equally by OI
 F and ALECSO). No application fee.\nDuration: Prize (one-time award).\n\nM
 ore: https://www.francophonie.org/prix-de-la-traduction-ibn-khaldoun-sengh
 or-442?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
