SUMMARY:Deadline: OIF: Support for Artist Mobility and Circulation of Cultu
 ral Goods 2026 (Francophonie)
DESCRIPTION:The OIF Support for Artist Mobility and Circulation of Cultural
  Goods programme provides grants of up to EUR 5\,000 for mobility (travel\
 , accommodation\, visa fees\, logistics) and up to EUR 2\,500 for circulat
 ion of cultural goods (excess baggage\, freight\, customs) within the Fran
 cophone zone\; both can be combined. ELIGIBILITY: professional artists and
  established artistic collectives with a demonstrated connection to the Fr
 ancophone space (by nationality\, working language\, or artistic collabora
 tions)\, residing in an OIF member state\, with minimum 2 years of experie
 nce in the cultural or artistic sector\; must directly manage the project 
 (not act as intermediaries)\; one application per individual per call. ELI
 GIBLE DISCIPLINES: live performance (music\, theatre\, dance\, comedy\, st
 orytelling)\, cinema/audiovisual\, literature/publishing\, and visual arts
 . PRIORITY given to projects promoting gender equality\, women artists\, c
 reators under 35\, and South-South mobility. Projects must take place betw
 een 25 March and 30 November 2026. Multiple selection sessions throughout 
 the year\; call open until 31 August 2026. Information webinars: 11 March\
 , 13 May\, and 8 July 2026 at 3 PM Paris time. Contact: culture.dlc@franco
 phonie.org. Apply at https://appelsaprojets.francophonie.org/fr/applicatio
 ns/soutien-a-la-circulation-des-biens-et-mobilite-des-artistes.\n\nOrganis
 ation: Organisation internationale de la Francophonie (OIF)\nLocation: Fra
 ncophone zone (OIF member states globally)\nAward: Up to EUR 5\,000 for ar
 tist mobility (travel\, accommodation\, visas\, logistics). Up to EUR 2\,5
 00 for circulation of cultural goods (excess baggage\, freight\, customs).
  Both can be combined. No application fee.\nDuration: Residencies or tours
  of 5 days to 3 months. Projects must take place between 25 March and 30 N
 ovember 2026.\n\nMore: https://appelsaprojets.francophonie.org/fr/applicat
 ions/soutien-a-la-circulation-des-biens-et-mobilite-des-artistes?utm_sourc
 e=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
