DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260731
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
SUMMARY:Deadline: Kometa Fellows 2026: Field Journalism\, Photography\, and
  Writing
DESCRIPTION:Kometa\, a French literary and journalism magazine\, awards fel
 lowships to journalists\, writers\, and photographers documenting reality 
 in contexts of war\, censorship\, or severe social and political tensions.
  Projects must be rooted in direct field experience and focused on contemp
 orary rather than historical events. Projects already under a contractual 
 agreement are ineligible. AMOUNT: €10\,000 per Fellow\, six Fellows sele
 cted. WHAT FELLOWS RECEIVE: one year of funding\; publication of the compl
 eted project (partial or full) in Kometa\; opportunity to contribute to th
 e monthly newsletter\; mentorship through editorial collaboration. 2026 FO
 CUS AREAS: disinformation and narrative wars\; political and social change
 s in the Gulf. DEADLINE: 31 July 2026. APPLY via the Tally form (https://t
 ally.so/r/J9XxMK)\, in French or English (about 30 to 45 minutes). Contact
 : fellows@kometarevue.com.\n\nOrganisation: Kometa (French literary and jo
 urnalism magazine)\nLocation: Remote / field-based (international)\nAward:
  €10\,000 per Fellow\, six Fellows selected. No application fee.\nDurati
 on: One year of funding for field work and research\n\nMore: https://komet
 arevue.com/page/fellows?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=r
 eferral
URL:https://kometarevue.com/page/fellows?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantd
 esk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote / field-based (international)
END:VEVENT
