SUMMARY:Deadline: Fulbright-Iméra Mediterranean Studies Award 2027-2028 (A
 ix-Marseille\, US Faculty)
DESCRIPTION:The Fulbright-Iméra Mediterranean Studies Award supports US fa
 culty to conduct research at the Iméra Institute for Advanced Study at Ai
 x Marseille Université. ELIGIBILITY: mid-career\, senior\, or community c
 ollege faculty affiliated with a US institution of higher education\; US c
 itizens residing outside France (permanent residents of France are ineligi
 ble)\; any discipline relating to Mediterranean studies\; English sufficie
 nt (French desirable). 1 or 2 grants awarded. PROVIDED: €2\,400/month st
 ipend\; fully equipped apartment with linens\; office in co-working space\
 ; visa fees waived\; academic event organisation expenses covered\; school
  placement assistance for dependents. DURATION: 5 or 10 months (September 
 2027 – June 2028\, flexible). DEADLINE: 15 September 2026. Apply via the
  Fulbright Scholar Program at https://fulbrightscholars.org/award/fulbrigh
 t-imera-mediterranean-studies-award-aix-marseille-university.\n\nOrganisat
 ion: Iméra – Aix Marseille Université\, in partnership with the Fulbri
 ght Commission\nLocation: Aix-Marseille\, France (campus residency)\nAward
 : €2\,400 (~USD 2\,600) monthly stipend\; fully covered accommodation (v
 alued USD 788–1\,966/month)\; €1\,200 (~USD 1\,300) travel allowance. 
 No application fee.\nDuration: 5 or 10 months (September 2027 – June 202
 8\, flexible start/end dates).\n\nMore: https://fulbrightscholars.org/awar
 d/fulbright-imera-mediterranean-studies-award-aix-marseille-university?utm
 _source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://fulbrightscholars.org/award/fulbright-imera-mediterranean-studi
 es-award-aix-marseille-university?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&ut
 m_medium=referral
