BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:govai-dc-winter-fellowship-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260712
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260713
SUMMARY:Deadline: GovAI DC Winter Fellowship 2027
DESCRIPTION:GovAI's DC Winter Fellowship is a three-month bipartisan in-per
 son fellowship in Washington\, DC\, designed for individuals seeking to en
 ter or advance in US AI governance and policy. The program emphasises bipa
 rtisan engagement\, rigorous analysis\, and practical policy relevance\, w
 ith a focus on how AI policy is shaped within the US political system. Fel
 lows conduct independent research on a topic of their choice with mentorsh
 ip from a GovAI supervisor\; the first two weeks explore the AI policy lan
 dscape before a research proposal is finalised. Outputs may include a repo
 rt\, white paper\, journal article\, op-ed\, or blog post targeted at an a
 udience relevant to AI policy. Fellows also attend expert Q&As\, skills wo
 rkshops\, seminars\, work-in-progress meetings\, and social events\, and a
 re encouraged to discuss follow-on career opportunities. GovAI alumni have
  gone on to roles in US government bodies (NSC\, OSTP\, Senate\, Departmen
 t of Commerce\, DHS)\; think tanks (CSIS\, CSET\, CNAS\, RAND\, Heritage F
 oundation\, FAI)\; AI companies (OpenAI\, Anthropic\, Google DeepMind)\; a
 nd universities (Yale\, Stanford\, MIT). AMOUNT: $21\,000 stipend for thre
 e months\, plus travel support to DC and weekday lunch. Part-time fellowsh
 ip at a pro-rated salary available for DC-based think tank researchers\, g
 overnment staffers\, or professionals doing AI governance work\; pay accom
 modations possible. ELIGIBILITY: candidates must have the right to work in
  the US\; no visa sponsorship. Open to a wide range of backgrounds (govern
 ment\, academia\, industry\, civil society)\; promising undergraduates wel
 come\; no strict degree requirements. Relevant areas include public policy
 \, political science\, engineering\, computer science\, economics\, biosec
 urity\, cybersecurity\, China studies\, and risk management. SELECTION CRI
 TERIA: quality and clarity of written work\, relevant expertise\, judgemen
 t\, and team fit. APPLICATION PROCESS: (1) written application and automat
 ed abstract reasoning assessment\; (2) paid remote work test (August 2026)
 \; (3) remote interview and reference checks (September 2026)\; decisions 
 communicated October 2026. Application deadline not yet publicly stated\; 
 applications open June 2026 -- check programme page for the deadline.\n\nO
 rganisation: Centre for the Governance of AI (GovAI)\nLocation: Washington
 \, DC\, USA\; in-person\, full-time (part-time possible for DC-based think
  tank or government staff).\nAward: $21\,000 stipend for the three-month t
 erm\, plus travel support to DC and weekday lunch provided. No visa sponso
 rship. No application fee.\nDuration: 3 months\, 18 January to 9 April 202
 7.\n\nMore: https://www.governance.ai/opportunities/dc-winter-fellowship-2
 027?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.governance.ai/opportunities/dc-winter-fellowship-2027?utm_s
 ource=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Washington\, DC\, USA\; in-person\, full-time (part-time possible 
 for DC-based think tank or government staff).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:anthropic-claude-corps-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260717
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260718
SUMMARY:Deadline: Claude Corps Fellowship
DESCRIPTION:Claude Corps is a national fellowship program from Anthropic pl
 acing early-career fellows full-time at nonprofits across America for one 
 year\, with the goal of extending AI's benefits to communities and buildin
 g fellows' AI skills. Anthropic funds the program and provides Claude expe
 rtise\; CodePath (America's largest collegiate CS education provider) is t
 he fellows' official employer of record and leads programming\; Social Fin
 ance leads measurement and evaluation. AMOUNT: $85\,000 full-time salary p
 lus benefits\; expansive Claude token budget\; relocation support as neede
 d. FELLOW EXPERIENCE: intensive Claude training at the start\; five hours 
 of ongoing weekly training throughout\; support from a CodePath mentor\; A
 nthropic office hours for technical questions\; and professional guidance 
 from the host organization manager. SAMPLE HOST ORGANIZATIONS: Braven (Chi
 cago)\, Code the Dream (Durham NC)\, Heartland Forward (Bentonville AR)\, 
 Montgomery County Food Bank (Conroe TX)\, Reef Environmental Education Fou
 ndation (Key Largo FL)\, StriveTogether (Cincinnati)\, YMCA of Greater Cha
 rlotte\, and more than 400 nonprofits total. ELIGIBILITY: anyone over 18 w
 ith under two years of full-time work experience\, regardless of education
 al background\; must be authorized to work in the US\; must be comfortable
  working with Claude and willing to relocate if necessary. COHORTS: Cohort
  1 (100 fellows\, starts October 2026) -- applications close 17 July 2026\
 ; Cohort 2 (starts January 2027) and Cohort 3 (starts August 2027) -- roll
 ing applications. Apply at https://www.anthropic.com/news/claude-corps.\n\
 nOrganisation: Anthropic (funded)\; CodePath (employer of record)\; Social
  Finance (evaluation)\nLocation: USA\; in-person at host nonprofit organiz
 ations across America (placement location varies\; relocation support avai
 lable).\nAward: $85\,000 full-time annual salary plus benefits\, expansive
  Claude token budget\, and relocation support as needed. No application fe
 e.\nDuration: 12 months.\n\nMore: https://www.anthropic.com/news/claude-co
 rps?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.anthropic.com/news/claude-corps?utm_source=artificialnouvea
 ugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:USA\; in-person at host nonprofit organizations across America (pl
 acement location varies\; relocation support available).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:sound-image-2026-call-for-works-greenwich@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260619
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260620
SUMMARY:Deadline: SOUND/IMAGE 2026: "Artistic Intelligence" - Call for Work
 s
DESCRIPTION:SOUND/IMAGE 2026 is the 11th edition of the University of Green
 wich festival exploring sound and image practice\, running 5-8 November 20
 26 in London. This year's theme is "Artistic Intelligence": a critical ref
 lection on creative choice\, agency\, and authenticity in the context of a
 lgorithmic and AI-mediated art making. The festival cites reference points
  from Vera Molnár\, Pauline Oliveros\, John Cage\, Iannis Xenakis\, Ryoji
  Ikeda\, and Refik Anadol. Special consideration is given to students\, ap
 prentices\, and emerging artists\; submissions are welcome from composers\
 , filmmakers\, artists\, performers\, and architects. CATEGORIES ACCEPTED:
  sound and music works\; audiovisual works\; talks\; artist statements\; w
 orkshops and practical demonstrations\; live performances\; installations.
  THEMATIC AREAS: embodied knowledge and lived experience in aesthetic judg
 ement\; creative choice vs chance encounters\; ownership\, authenticity\, 
 and AI co-creation\; human and algorithmic capability\; spatial and immers
 ive audio-visual forms\; interdisciplinary practice (CreaTech)\; practice 
 research. SUBMISSION RULES: works under 15 minutes in duration (installati
 ons exempt from duration limit)\; maximum three submissions per artist acr
 oss all categories\; artists must attend and present in person\; submit se
 parately for each submission via Microsoft CMT. FESTIVAL PASS: all accepte
 d artists must purchase a festival pass at a reduced rate of £25. Notific
 ations before end of July 2026. Deadline: 19 June 2026\, 23:59 UTC+1 (exte
 nded from 12 June). Submit at https://blogs.gre.ac.uk/sound-image/sound-im
 age-2026-call-for-works/.\n\nOrganisation: University of Greenwich\nLocati
 on: University of Greenwich\, London\, UK\; in-person attendance required.
 \nAward: No payment to artists. All accepted artists must purchase a festi
 val pass at a reduced rate of £25 (covers catering and technical support)
 .\nDuration: Festival runs 5-8 November 2026.\n\nMore: https://blogs.gre.a
 c.uk/sound-image/sound-image-2026-call-for-works/?utm_source=artificialnou
 veaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://blogs.gre.ac.uk/sound-image/sound-image-2026-call-for-works/?ut
 m_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:University of Greenwich\, London\, UK\; in-person attendance requi
 red.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:revitalizing-rituals-2026-open-call@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260719
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260720
SUMMARY:Deadline: Revitalizing Rituals 2026 Open Call
DESCRIPTION:Revitalizing Rituals invites artists from all disciplines -- so
 und\, movement\, visual arts\, installation\, performance\, and transdisci
 plinary practices -- to join a research-creation journey across two landsc
 apes: Bhar Lazreg in Tunisia and the wetlands of Somogy County in Hungary.
  The project explores rituals as living forms of belonging: reconnecting c
 ommunities\, land\, memory\, food\, ecological reciprocity\, and the more-
 than-human world. Selected artists work with local communities as co-parti
 cipants in a shared inquiry into moving from extraction toward reciprocity
 . Organised by Homo Faber Alapítvány (Hungary). AMOUNT: EUR 6\,000 gross
  artist fee and production budget\; international travel and per diems cov
 ered\; on-site accommodation provided. ELIGIBILITY: minimum 5 years of act
 ive artistic practice\; portfolio reflecting interest in situated or relat
 ional work\; no formal degree required\; working language is English (loca
 l language navigation valued)\; must be available for the full residency c
 ycle including all international travel\; must be able to legally receive 
 the fee and invoice the organising partners from country of residence. Str
 ongly encourages applications from historically marginalised or underrepre
 sented voices. KEY DATES: Application Deadline 19 July 2026 (midnight) -- 
 note the open call PDF also references a 5 July date\; the officially prom
 oted deadline is 19 July\; Online Q&A 29 June 2026\, 14:00 Tunisia / 15:00
  CET (register at https://forms.gle/brnZvXvFe4JB8zL26)\; Online Conversati
 ons with shortlisted artists: mid July to mid August 2026\; Selection Resu
 lts: 31 August 2026\; Placemaking Camp: 1 week\, end of November 2026\, Hu
 ngary\; Storytellers Camp: 1 week\, March 2027\, Tunisia\; Residency Perio
 d: minimum 1 month (splittable)\, April to July 2027\; Final Presentation:
  August 2027\; Closing Event: 3 days\, winter/early spring 2028\, Hungary.
  Apply via the open call form linked at https://homofaber.hu/wp-content/up
 loads/2026/06/Artist-Open-Call-FINAL-in-the-RR-form.pdf.\n\nOrganisation: 
 Homo Faber Alapítvány (Homo Faber Foundation)\nLocation: Bhar Lazreg\, T
 unisia and Somogy County\, Hungary\; multi-stage in-person residency acros
 s both sites.\nAward: EUR 6\,000 gross artist fee and production budget\; 
 international travel and per diems covered\; on-site accommodation provide
 d. No application fee.\nDuration: Multi-stage residency: Placemaking Camp 
 (1 week\, November 2026\, Hungary)\; Storytellers Camp (1 week\, March 202
 7\, Tunisia)\; Residency Period (minimum 1 month\, April-July 2027)\; publ
 ic presentation (August 2027)\; Closing Event (3 days\, winter/early sprin
 g 2028\, Hungary).\n\nMore: https://homofaber.hu/wp-content/uploads/2026/0
 6/Artist-Open-Call-FINAL-in-the-RR-form.pdf?utm_source=artificialnouveaugr
 antdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://homofaber.hu/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Artist-Open-Call-FINAL-
 in-the-RR-form.pdf?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referr
 al
LOCATION:Bhar Lazreg\, Tunisia and Somogy County\, Hungary\; multi-stage in
 -person residency across both sites.
END:VEVENT
