DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261215
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261216
SUMMARY:Deadline: NEH: Collections Stewardship (December 2026 cycle)
DESCRIPTION:NEH Collections Stewardship funds preservation projects at libr
 aries\, archives\, museums\, colleges/universities\, and preservation-serv
 ices organisations. Eligible activities include digitisation and reformatt
 ing of collections for public access through digital repositories\, preser
 vation planning\, and environmental assessments. Relevant for organisation
 s working with born-digital or digitally reformatted collections including
  software\, AI artefacts\, and digital cultural heritage. Applications for
  the December 2026 cycle open 31 August 2026\; deadline 15 December 2026. 
 A May 2026 cycle has already passed. ELIGIBILITY: institutional applicants
  only (libraries\, archives\, museums\, colleges\, universities\, preserva
 tion-services organisations based in the US)\; individual researchers and 
 for-profit entities are not eligible. Apply via grants.gov.\n\nOrganisatio
 n: National Endowment for the Humanities (NEH)\nLocation: United States. A
 pplicants must be US-based institutions.\nAward: Up to $350\,000 for singl
 e organizations\; up to $500\,000 for consortia. Projects up to 3 years. N
 o application fee.\nDuration: Up to 3 years.\n\nMore: https://www.neh.gov/
 program/collections-stewardship?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
URL:https://www.neh.gov/program/collections-stewardship?utm_source=artifici
 alnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:United States. Applicants must be US-based institutions.
END:VEVENT
