UID:freelands-learning-through-making-fund-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260911
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260912
SUMMARY:Deadline: Freelands Foundation: Learning Through Making Fund
DESCRIPTION:The Learning Through Making fund supports UK-based visual art o
 rganisations to bring opportunities for making and material exploration in
 to their art education work. Freelands Foundation is looking for explorato
 ry projects that embrace openness\, collaboration\, and iteration -- enabl
 ing organisations to work with materials in an expansive way\, unpicking p
 reconceptions about making and material literacy without predefined outcom
 es. ELIGIBLE ACTIVITIES: providing materials\, transport\, or access to ex
 pertise and facilities\; action-research trials such as a new series of wo
 rkshops or events developing material literacy\; adding a making-focused e
 lement to existing activity. Projects may range from a few days to several
  months\, but must take place between 1 January and 31 December 2027. AMOU
 NT: up to £25\,000\; funding provided no earlier than December 2026. ELIG
 IBILITY: UK-based visual art organisations run with a charitable purpose a
 nd for public benefit\; eligible types include charities registered in Eng
 land and Wales\, Scotland\, or Northern Ireland\; exempt charities\; galle
 ries\, museums\, or organisations within a Local Authority or larger chari
 table body (e.g. universities)\; and Community Interest Companies or Commu
 nity Benefit Societies meeting specific criteria (charitable purposes\, as
 set lock\, no dividend distribution\, ability to segregate restricted fund
 s). Organisations with a prior Freelands Foundation grant relationship are
  eligible\; you may not apply for activity already funded by Freelands Fou
 ndation. Individuals are not eligible. HOW TO APPLY: download the Applicat
 ion Form\, Application Guidance\, and optional Access Form from freelandsf
 oundation.co.uk\; email completed form to grants@freelandsfoundation.co.uk
  with subject line 'LTM Fund - Application'\; one additional page of image
 s or diagrams may be included. APPLICATION SUPPORT SESSIONS (online): 9 Ju
 ly 2026\, 10:30am-12pm\; 12 August 2026\, 10:30am-12pm. KEY DATES: applica
 tions open 17 June 2026\; close 11 September 2026 at 12pm\; outcomes share
 d 23 November 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Freelands Foundation\nLocation: UK (E
 ngland\, Northern Ireland\, Scotland\, Wales)\; activity must occur within
  the United Kingdom.\nAward: Up to £25\,000. No application fee.\nDuratio
 n: Projects of any length\, taking place between 1 January and 31 December
  2027. Funding provided no earlier than December 2026.\n\nMore: https://fr
 eelandsfoundation.co.uk/engage/apply/grants/learning-through-making-fund?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://freelandsfoundation.co.uk/engage/apply/grants/learning-through-
 making-fund?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:UK (England\, Northern Ireland\, Scotland\, Wales)\; activity must
  occur within the United Kingdom.
END:VEVENT
