 nouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Deadline: Ucross Fellowship for Native American Visual Artists: Spr
 ing 2027
DESCRIPTION:The Ucross Fellowship for Native American Visual Artists is a d
 edicated fellowship within Ucross Foundation's residency program\, offerin
 g fully funded time and space to make work on a working cattle ranch in th
 e foothills of Wyoming's Bighorn Mountains. The fellowship provides living
  accommodations\, meals\, and work space at no charge\, with no applicatio
 n fee. One Fellowship winner is selected per session\; all applicants also
  have the option of being considered for a general Ucross residency. ELIGI
 BILITY: open to Native American visual artists who are practicing contempo
 rary artists currently producing work in any visual medium\, including but
  not limited to painting\, drawing\, mixed media\, sculpture\, printmaking
 \, photography\, video\, animation\, performance art\, installation\, and 
 ceramics\; and who are enrolled members of a state-recognized or federally
 -recognized Tribe\, Pueblo\, Nation\, Native Community\, Political Entity\
 , or Alaskan Native Village. The work sample and project description are t
 he most significant features of the application. Unless the work is interd
 isciplinary\, applicants are encouraged to apply in a single primary disci
 pline and submit a work sample and project description emphasizing that di
 scipline. Work-sample requirements: VISUAL ARTWORK\, submit 10 images (JPE
 G format\, no PDFs) with file names including title and size\, plus a data
  sheet listing title\, medium\, size\, and year of completion for each ima
 ge\; FILM/VIDEO/ANIMATION/PERFORMANCE\, submit up to 3 video files (each u
 nder 8 minutes and smaller than 200 MB) or up to 3 Vimeo or YouTube links.
  The open call for the Spring 2027 session closes July 15\, 2026 (apply by
  11:59 p.m. MT). A separate Ucross Fellowship for Native American Writers 
 is also offered.\n\nOrganisation: Ucross Foundation\nLocation: Sheridan\, 
 Wyoming\, USA\nAward: Fully funded fellowship residency\; living accommoda
 tions\, meals\, and work space provided. No application fee.\nDuration: Sp
 ring session (February through early June 2027)\; residencies range from t
 wo to six weeks\n\nMore: https://www.ucrossfoundation.org/residency-progra
 m.html?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
