UID:chornobyl40-open-call-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260712
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260713
SUMMARY:Deadline: Chornobyl40: Open Call 2026 (Virtual Residency & Internat
 ional Exhibition)
DESCRIPTION:Chornobyl40 is a European artistic program\, funded by the Euro
 pean Union\, exploring the multiple legacies of the Chornobyl disaster not
  only as a past event but as an ongoing condition shaping the present and 
 future. The open call invites artists\, designers\, researchers\, collecti
 ves\, and interdisciplinary/hybrid practitioners to engage with Chornobyl 
 as a landscape\, a memory\, a political reality\, and a speculative horizo
 n. This is a call for interpretation\, friction\, and critical imagination
 \, not illustration. STRUCTURE (three phases): PHASE 1\, VIRTUAL RESIDENCY
 : 40 selected participants\, September-October 2026\, online\, weekly sess
 ions (Tuesdays 14:00-18:00 CET)\, 30 hours total with minimum 90% attendan
 ce\; a structured process from idea to concept to pre-production including
  talks on Chornobyl\, ecology\, and contaminated territories\, encounters 
 with artists and technologists\, a Concept Creation Hackathon\, an XR Conc
 ept Development Workshop (exploratory\, non-technical)\, a Mental Health &
  Eco-Anxiety Lab (4h)\, collective discussions\, peer feedback\, and tailo
 red mentoring. PHASE 2\, SELECTION & PRODUCTION: 20 projects selected (bas
 ed on a video presentation\, project documentation\, and a live pitch) rec
 eive production support. PHASE 3\, EXHIBITIONS: the 20 projects tour a Eur
 opean exhibition in 2027 (Madrid\, Berlin\, Toulouse\, Kyiv)\; artist pres
 ence optional but encouraged. WHAT'S OFFERED: for the 40 participants\, ac
 cess to a curated residency\, talks\, workshops\, mentoring\, and a Europe
 an network\; for the 20 selected projects\, a EUR 500 grant (fully digital
  works) or EUR 1\,000 grant (installations needing physical materials) plu
 s exhibition inclusion (travel\, accommodation\, and transport not covered
 ). WHO CAN APPLY: artists\, designers\, researchers\, collectives\, and in
 terdisciplinary/hybrid practices\; open internationally\, no age limit\, e
 merging and established profiles equally encouraged. PROJECT THEMES: ecolo
 gy and post-disaster environments\, memory and trauma\, geopolitical narra
 tives\, invisible forces (radiation\, data\, systems)\, technological imag
 inaries\, nuclear energy\, and misinformation and perception\; projects mu
 st relate to Chornobyl (directly or indirectly)\, be adaptable to multiple
  exhibition contexts\, and consider eco-responsibility\; new and adapted e
 xisting works both welcome. SELECTION CRITERIA (equally weighted): artisti
 c quality\, relevance to the manifesto\, eco-responsibility\, digital dime
 nsion\, and emotional and critical impact. TIMELINE: open call launched 19
  May 2026\; application deadline 12 July 2026\; 40 participants announced 
 end of July 2026. HOW TO APPLY: submit in English via the Google Form with
  a bio/CV link\, portfolio link\, and a project proposal (PDF\, 2 A4 pages
  maximum). Application is free. Questions: contact@gate22.net.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: Chornobyl40 (gate22 / European Institute of Chornobyl consortium)\nL
 ocation: Online residency (weekly sessions Tuesdays 14:00-18:00 CET)\; Eur
 opean touring exhibition 2027 in Madrid\, Berlin\, Toulouse\, and Kyiv. Op
 en internationally.\nAward: Residency is free to attend. For the 20 projec
 ts selected for production: EUR 500 grant for fully digital works or EUR 1
 \,000 grant for installations requiring physical materials\, plus inclusio
 n in the international exhibition. Travel\, accommodation\, and transport 
 are not covered. No application fee.\nDuration: Phase 1 virtual residency 
 September-October 2026 (weekly Tuesday sessions\, 30 hours total\, minimum
  90% attendance). Phase 2 selection and production. Phase 3 European touri
 ng exhibition in 2027.\n\nMore: https://forms.gle/5btrxy7LwfY8QyFW6?utm_so
 urce=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://forms.gle/5btrxy7LwfY8QyFW6?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantde
 sk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Online residency (weekly sessions Tuesdays 14:00-18:00 CET)\; Euro
 pean touring exhibition 2027 in Madrid\, Berlin\, Toulouse\, and Kyiv. Ope
 n internationally.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
