UID:prospect-art-new-work-we-come-in-pieces-2027@artificialnouveau.github.i
 o
DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260816
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260817
SUMMARY:Deadline: Prospect Art: NEW WORK Commission 2027 - "We Come in Piec
 es"
DESCRIPTION:Prospect Art invites visual artists worldwide to apply for the 
 2027 NEW WORK commission\, a USD 1\,500 project grant supporting the creat
 ion of a new\, conceptually driven work responding to the curatorial theme
  "We Come in Pieces\," developed by 2026-2027 Curatorial Fellow Alma Samme
 l. Through a single application\, artists are also considered for ONE WORK
  (an online series featuring an in-depth conversation centered on a single
  completed artwork) and BROADCAST (a curated online program of screenings\
 , artist talks\, and discussions). THEME: "We Come in Pieces" proposes the
  Alien as a method for shifting perspective\, approaching alienness as a p
 ractice of estrangement to encounter the world beyond familiar human-cente
 red narratives. It explores relationships between human and more-than-huma
 n worlds\, speculative cosmologies\, ecological systems\, technologies\, l
 andscapes\, histories\, infrastructures\, and nonhuman forms of intelligen
 ce (satellites and orbital debris\, fungal networks\, oceans\, atmospheric
  systems\, algorithmic intelligences)\, inviting works that displace the p
 oint of listening\, seeing\, sensing\, or knowing. Research-based and conc
 eptually driven practices are especially encouraged. WHAT'S OFFERED: NEW W
 ORK\, USD 1\,500 to one artist plus a featured website section and social 
 promotion (project completed within 12 months)\; ONE WORK\, a published ar
 ticle and social promotion\; BROADCAST\, a USD 125 screening or speaking f
 ee and inclusion in a themed program. ELIGIBILITY: professional visual art
 ists working in any medium at any career stage\, except those currently en
 rolled in undergraduate or graduate studio art programs\; collectives may 
 apply. Media welcomed include moving image\, installation\, sculpture\, ph
 otography\, performance\, sound\, digital media\, social practice\, and in
 terdisciplinary forms. APPLICATION: submit via the official Google Form wi
 th contact information\, a project description (250 words)\, a sketch/visu
 alization (1-3 images)\, up to 3 links to completed work samples\, a state
 ment relating the project to the theme (200 words)\, a short bio and exhib
 ition history (500 words)\, and a budget breakdown of the USD 1\,500. A US
 D 10 administrative fee is paid via PayPal (include PayPal name and transa
 ction ID)\; a fee waiver is available with no explanation by emailing subm
 issions@prospectart.org before the deadline. Writers may email gioj@prospe
 ctart.org with samples. DEADLINE: 16 August 2026\; results for the NEW WOR
 K grant notified by end of September. INFO SESSION: 5 August 2026 at noon 
 PST.\n\nOrganisation: Prospect Art\nLocation: Remote / online. Open to vis
 ual artists worldwide\; programs (ONE WORK\, BROADCAST) run online.\nAward
 : NEW WORK: USD 1\,500 commission for one artist\, plus a featured website
  section and social promotion. BROADCAST: USD 125 screening or speaking fe
 e if selected. ONE WORK: a published article (exposure). NOTE: a USD 10 ad
 ministrative fee applies to apply\, with a no-questions-asked waiver avail
 able on request before the deadline. PayPal account required to receive fu
 nds.\nDuration: The commissioned NEW WORK project should be completed with
 in twelve months of selection.\n\nMore: https://www.prospectart.org/new-wo
 rk-grant?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.prospectart.org/new-work-grant?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote / online. Open to visual artists worldwide\; programs (ONE 
 WORK\, BROADCAST) run online.
END:VEVENT
