DTSTAMP:20260709T211504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261103
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261104
SUMMARY:Deadline: Royal Academy of Fine Arts Antwerp: Call for Two-Year Res
 earch Proposals (2027 start)
DESCRIPTION:The Royal Academy of Fine Arts Antwerp (AP University of Applie
 d Sciences and Arts) invites applications for two-year artistic research p
 rojects starting 20 September 2027. Two-year research projects provide 55%
  employment for the research assignment over 24 months (as a contractual p
 roject staff member) plus EUR 2\,000 in operating funds (EUR 1\,000 per pr
 oject year). Proposals are developed in collaboration with the Academy's r
 esearch groups and must align with\, endorse\, and further develop the mis
 sion and vision of the Royal Academy of Fine Arts Antwerp. PRECONDITIONS: 
 the proposal must be in line with the Academy's mission/vision\; the appli
 cant must be legally employable by the Royal Academy of Fine Arts Antwerp/
 AP Hogeschool on a contractual basis\; and\, at the time of application\, 
 the applicant must hold a Master's degree in Visual Arts awarded by a Belg
 ian higher education institution (a non-Belgian degree is possible only if
  validated or recognised through the NARIC procedure\, with proof included
  or a declared willingness to undergo it). PROCEDURE (two steps): STEP 1\,
  apply via the Expression of Interest form sent to research_royalacademyan
 twerp@ap.be before 3 November 2026\, 12:00 noon (applicants informed no la
 ter than end November 2026 whether they may develop a full dossier)\; STEP
  2\, submit the full dossier via the two-year project application form bef
 ore 1 February 2027\, 12:00 noon. Evaluation by an independent reading com
 mittee aims to conclude in May 2027. Contact: research_royalacademyantwerp
 @ap.be.\n\nOrganisation: Royal Academy of Fine Arts Antwerp (AP University
  of Applied Sciences and Arts)\nLocation: Antwerp\, Belgium. Salaried rese
 arch position\; applicant must be legally employable in Belgium.\nAward: T
 wo-year research projects: 55% employment for the research assignment over
  24 months (contractual project staff member) plus EUR 2\,000 in operating
  funds (EUR 1\,000 per project year). No application fee.\nDuration: Two-y
 ear projects (24 months). Projects start at the earliest 20 September 2027
 .\n\nMore: https://www.ap-arts.be/en/submit-research-proposal-royal-academ
 y-fine-arts-antwerp?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=refer
 ral
URL:https://www.ap-arts.be/en/submit-research-proposal-royal-academy-fine-a
 rts-antwerp?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Antwerp\, Belgium. Salaried research position\; applicant must be 
 legally employable in Belgium.
